        Shoe Carnival opens in Crockett Square
    



            Jul 28, 2017
        Updated 59 min ago


















































































Shoe Carnival is opening a new store in Morristown just in time for tax free savings. Shoe Carnival brings an exciting and unique shopping experience to the area. Customers will enjoy an open floor plan, catchy music and friendly associates, coupled with great values on name brand shoes and accessories.The fun begins at 9 a.m. on Saturday, July 29 at the new Shoe Carnival store in Morristown, located off Crockett Trace Drive and College Park Drive, near Hobby Lobby and Ross.The first 100 customers in the door at 9 a.m. on Saturday, age 18 and over, will receive a $10 reward card to use toward anything in the store. Other special events during the day include:

• A 10 a.m. drawing for free shoes for a year• An 11 a.m. drawing for $1,000 cash courtesy of Crocs• A drawing for a $100 Shoe Carnival shopping spree every hour noon-5 p.m.

• Doorbuster deals from 9 a.m. to noon• Even more prizes and giveaways on Sunday“We are excited to open a new Shoe Carnival in Morristown. Shoe Carnival is known for our one of a kind shopping experience, unbelievable product assortment and unique atmosphere, which creates a customer focused way to shop for shoes,” says Todd Beurman, Senior Vice President of Marketing. “At Shoe Carnival, our customers will not only be treated to great value on name brand footwear and accessories for the entire family, they’ll also get a fun and exciting shopping experience.”The Shoe Carnival shopping experience offers excellent values on name brand shoes like Nike, Skechers, Fila, Adidas, Sperry and many more. Shoe Carnival stores are home to an exciting environment and a staff dedicated to meeting customer needs every day. Shoe Carnival’s spontaneity and family focus is what sets them apart from other shoe stores, and makes shoe shopping as fun as it should be. For more details on Shoe Carnival grand openings and giveaway information, visit www.shoecarnival.com/grandopening.

















































